description: List the datasets that you have configured in this Region. For more information about datasets, see Flywheel overview in the Amazon Comprehend Developer Guide.

parameters.name: Filter
parameters.description: Filters the datasets to be returned in the response. Status (string) --- Filter the datasets based on the dataset status. DatasetType (string) --- Filter the datasets based on the dataset type. CreationTimeAfter (datetime) --- Filter the datasets to include datasets created after the specified time. CreationTimeBefore (datetime) --- Filter the datasets to include datasets created before the specified time.

nested_params.name: Status
nested_params.description: Filter the datasets based on the dataset status.

nested_params.name: DatasetType
nested_params.description: Filter the datasets based on the dataset type.

nested_params.name: CreationTimeAfter
nested_params.description: Filter the datasets to include datasets created after the specified time.

nested_params.name: CreationTimeBefore
nested_params.description: Filter the datasets to include datasets created before the specified time.

nested_items.name: DatasetType
nested_items.description: The dataset type (training data or test data).

nested_items.name: DatasetS3Uri
nested_items.description: The S3 URI where the dataset is stored.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The dataset status. While the system creates the dataset, the status is CREATING. When the dataset is ready to use, the status changes to COMPLETED.

nested_items.name: Message
nested_items.description: A description of the status of the dataset.

nested_items.name: NumberOfDocuments
nested_items.description: The number of documents in the dataset.

nested_items.name: EndTime
nested_items.description: Time when the data from the dataset becomes available in the data lake.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: Identifies the next page of results to return.
